sql:
SELECT COUNT(score_id)
FROM happiness_scores
WHERE happiness_score > (SELECT AVG(happiness_score) FROM happiness_scores);

external_knowledge:
- "Corruption perception index" is a measure of the perceived levels of public sector corruption in a country;
- "Happiness score" is a measure of the overall happiness and well-being of a country's population;
- The ranks are based on the average values of these scores and indices.

- "first few regions" refers to regions with IDs 1, 2, and 3;
- "higher perception of corruption" corresponds to a corruption perception index greater than 0.7;
- "multiple records of governance indicators" means more than one record of corruption perception data.

- "regions of interest" refers to regions with IDs 1, 2, and 3;
- "bloomed" refers to countries with an average happiness score greater than 6.5;
- "perceived corruption levels" refers to the corruption perception index.
